 nowrap><b><font color='white' face='Verdana' size='2'>Kuotat</font></b></td>
        <TD bgcolor='black' valign='top'><font color='white' face='Verdana' size='2'> This happens effect happens with all insta-click items.  </P><P>Cast any spell and the spell jewels take about 3 seconds to refresh.  If you click on an insta-click item, the spell jewels automatically refresh (unless the spell cast has a long reload time, eg QVoX).</P><P>You can then immediatly cast the next spell.  </P><P>This is a known bug and not, to my knowledge considered an exploit.</P><P>There is a bug with this though.  If you cast a spell then insta-click the "jewel refresh" away and cast a low cast time spell (PE or something else with a REALLY quick cast time), you get the message "spell recovery time not met", and the spell does not cast.  If you cast a spell that has a longer cast time then 3 seconds or wait a second after doing the clicky thing, you can cast the faster cast spells.  </P><P>It's been around since the dawn of time, that I know of and it effects all insta click items.</P><P><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=95266" target="_blank">Kuotat Smith</a><BR><s>Warlock</s> Witch<BR>Mithaniel Marr</font></td>
